To summarize, our technical contributions are:
We present NSVF that consists of a set of voxel-bounded implicit ﬁelds, where for each voxel, voxel embeddings are learned to encode local properties for high-quality rendering;
NSVF utilizes the sparse voxel structure to achieve efﬁcient rendering;
We introduce a progressive training strategy that efﬁciently learns the underlying sparse voxel structure with a differentiable ray-marching operation from a set of posed 2D images in an end-to-end manner.
